The Hong Kong government said on Sunday that it will slaughter all chickens in local chicken farms and all poultry at wholesale markets and retail outlets in an attempt to get rid of the source of influenza A H5N1 virus or "bird flu".
Test results related to the first bird flu case detected in a human suggested that the main mode of influenza A H5N1 virus transmission was bird-to-human, it was known here Saturday.
Although the deadly H5N1 virus has killed several patients in Hong Kong, no case of bird flu was reported in Macao.
